When to Use FormRecord

Use FormRecord when:

1.Control names are dynamic

2.Keys come from API responses

3.Form structure is key-value based

4.Users can add custom fields

When Not to Use FormRecord

Avoid using FormRecord when:

1.Form fields are fixed → use FormGroup

2.Data is an ordered list → use FormArray

3.Form structure is static


Key Concept to Remember

The easiest way to remember FormRecord:

FormGroup → fixed object structure
FormArray → indexed list structure
FormRecord → dynamic object structure

